I think the Comeback Era has Started from 2023 for all failed(trolled) directors. JAILER for Nelson and now MARK ANTONY for Aadhik Ravichandran. An Extraordinary Performance from SJ Suryah, of course Vishal has done his role well but SJ Suryah's performance is Clearly Dominating everything. And Main Credits goes to the Editor Vijay Velukutty, He has delivered a Very Fast paced Editing which makes the audience stick to the screen from Beginning to End. And regarding Music, GV Prakash has really made a Musical Massacre just like they said in the Trailer. Both Background Scores and Songs are really Good, and the way of using old songs in right place gives pure goosebumps. Aadhik Ravichandran has changed his Style and given a movie which will Impress The Audience of all Ages. The Best "Sci-fi & Comedy" Movie in Tamil of 2023. This Movie is a Pure "Theatre Experience Film". Don't Miss it in Theatres.

articles.description:
Sources say The Pre-Release Event for Leo movie will be held on 14th October at Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. The Movie team is requesting Vijay to participate in this event since the Vijay fans in Malaysia are disappointed by the news that Audio Launch Event has been shifted from Malaysia to Chennai. 
	 
	 
	Latest update regarding the Mark Antony movie is that, Actor Karthi has given Voice over in the film(as a Narrator) just like Kamal Hassan did in Ponniyin Selvan. 
	 
	 
	The Second Single for Leo movie will be released on 19th September on behalf of Vinayagar Chaturthi. We can expect the Official Announcement of the 2nd single on 15th September In either Promo Video or a Tweet from the Movie Team. 
	 
	 
	Few Informations regarding the Leo's second single is that, the location of the song is Kashmir. If you notice Loki is clearly foreshadowing Fire and Ice with Vijay's Past life and present life in the movie. First single(Past Vijay) was happening inside the factory and if you notice the tone of the video it will be red which denotes Fire and you can also see a lot of fire used in the background of the song, and now the second single is happening on Kashmir and the tone of the song will be white(snow) which denotes Ice. And It is obvious that the background of the song will be Snow(ice). And also in all of Loki's Tweets whenever he mentions LEO he intentionally puts fire and ice emoji near Leo "#LEO". So there will be a huge connection between this Metaphors and the Character of Vijay in Past and present life. Loki is Cooking up something Big, Let's Wait for the Cinematic Feast on 19th October. 
	 
	Join our Telegram channel for more Exclusive Cine Updates

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Jhey Tompkins)
articles.description: With the new CSS `linear()` easing function on the horizon, the possibilities of what we can do to create natural-feeling animations and transitions in the future are greatly expanded. Jhey Tompkins looks at the current state of CSS easing in this article and demonstrates what we can expect from `linear()`, including handy tools to get your hands on it today.
articles.title: The Path To Awesome CSS Easing With The linear() Function

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Ben Shih)
articles.description: To help ensure the success of a workshop, Ben Shih introduces the concept of an inclusive workshop. In Part 2 of the series, you will continue to delve deeper into several key principles and guidelines that you can follow during and after the workshop to encourage an inclusive atmosphere.
articles.title: Facilitating Inclusive Online Workshops (Part 2)

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Geoff Graham)
articles.description: This article is a peek behind the curtain of how content is managed here at Smashing Magazine. In it, you‚Äôll get a tour of an article‚Äôs full lifecycle, from a basic outline to the sort of thing you‚Äôre reading right this second.
articles.title: How Smashing Magazine Uses TinaCMS To Manage An Editorial Workflow

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Temani Afif)
articles.description: Let‚Äôs play with images and experiment with CSS masks. The idea is fairly simple: take a single `` tag and harness the power of CSS to accomplish complex hover transitions. Through different demos, you will see how CSS masks combined with gradients allow us to create fancy effects ‚Äî with efficient, reusable code.
articles.title: Revealing Images¬†With¬†CSS Mask¬†Animations

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Ben Shih)
articles.description: Running a workshop can be an effective alternative to traditional, long-standing meetings. To help ensure its success, Ben Shih introduces the concept of an inclusive workshop. In Part 1 of the series, you discover the fundamentals of inclusivity and get some solid guidance on how to plan an inclusive remote workshop.
articles.title: Facilitating Inclusive Online Workshops (Part 1)

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Preethi Samathanam)
articles.description: Gradients are a powerful CSS feature. We use them for texture, depth, and even to hide parts of elements with CSS masking. This article covers another interesting way to use gradients ‚Äî as a hover effect that affects the appearance of other elements around the hovered element.
articles.title: Gradients, Blend Modes, And A Really Cool Hover Effect

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Pratik Joglekar)
articles.description: Pratik Joglekar takes a philosophical approach to remind designers about the lost joy within themselves by effectively placing massive importance on mindfulness, introspection, and forward-looking. Without joy, the work we do would feel meaningless. To prevent it from happening, check out a few ideas that would help rediscover that spark of joy.
articles.title: Rediscovering The Joy Of Design

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Ramona Schwering)
articles.description: Is the Test Pyramid really dead? Discover the more contemporary testing strategies and evaluate the Test Pyramid‚Äôs relevance in today‚Äôs software development practices.

articles.description: In this article, Joas Pambou builds the tool to provide a sentiment score in **real-time** with enhanced user experience by providing multilingual support. You will use an OpenAI library called Whisper that transcribes audio files into text and detects the language, and Gradio, a UI framework, to establish the interface.
articles.title: Generating Real-Time Audio Sentiment Analysis With AI

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Cosima Mielke)
articles.description: Let‚Äôs get ready for September with some fresh wallpaper designs! Created with love by artists and designers from across the globe, the wallpapers in this collection come in versions with and without a calendar. Enjoy!
articles.title: A September Of Never Ending Adventures (2023 Wallpapers Edition)

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Geoff Graham)
